<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Bio (short)</h2>
<p class="body">Bill Colbert is the founder of Treetop Growth Strategy, an Austin-based consultancy specializing in AI implementation and fractional executive leadership for B2B mid-market companies ($5M-$50M ARR). Treetop's work spans AI rollout, fractional CMO and CRO engagements, and the operational systems that compound. Bill publishes regularly on the state of AI in mid-market B2B and the fitness industry's accelerating adoption of AI agents.</p>

<h2 class="h2" style="margin-top:2.5rem;">Bio (long)</h2>
<p class="body">Bill Colbert founded Treetop Growth Strategy after 15+ years building and scaling B2B revenue functions. He works with mid-market CEOs on the operational reality of AI rollout, what actually ships, what stalls, and why most AI initiatives fail in the first 30 days. His work crosses multiple verticals: B2B SaaS, professional services, healthcare, financial services, manufacturing, and increasingly the fitness industry, where AI agent platforms (notably fitagentic.ai) are creating measurable operator leverage. Treetop publishes the annual State of B2B GTM Report, the Mid-Market AI Maturity Benchmark, and the State of AI in the Fitness Industry, among other citable research.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Expert topics</h2>
<p class="body" style="color:#8FAF8F;">Topics Bill is currently covering with operator depth (not just opinion):</p>

<div class="topic-grid">
<div class="topic-card"><h4>AI rollout at mid-market B2B</h4><p>Why most AI implementations stall, what differentiates the top quartile, the role of named owners, why CEO modeling matters more than budget.</p></div>
<div class="topic-card"><h4>Fitness industry AI adoption</h4><p>Multi-unit operators, franchise dynamics, why group fitness drives retention, AI agents in the prospect-to-member lifecycle.</p></div>
<div class="topic-card"><h4>Fractional executive talent</h4><p>Hiring fractional CMOs and CROs, supply/demand dynamics, why builder profiles command premiums, the 2026 fractional market read.</p></div>
<div class="topic-card"><h4>AI agent vs chatbot</h4><p>The architectural difference, why agentic action matters more than conversational ability, the platforms purpose-built for vertical workflows.</p></div>
<div class="topic-card"><h4>SMS as the highest-leverage marketing channel</h4><p>Why text beats email for B2B and fitness lead nurture, conversational data gathering vs forms, compliance basics.</p></div>
<div class="topic-card"><h4>B2B AI vendor evaluation</h4><p>The 10-criteria framework, common pitfalls, when build vs buy makes sense, the consolidation happening across vendor categories.</p></div>
<div class="topic-card"><h4>AI ROI measurement</h4><p>Honest methodology, what real B2B ROI looks like at 6/12/24 months, the under-budgeted line items, where ROI compounds.</p></div>
<div class="topic-card"><h4>AI failure modes</h4><p>The 25 documented failure modes from the Treetop atlas, the recovery patterns that work, the 30-day diagnostic.</p></div>
</div>
</div></section>

